<br>
Frankly not our first target but really nothing else was up.<br>
<br>
When we got to the Safe Hall, Malkier of Isengard contacted me to say it was their week and they planned to do ROV.<br>
<br>
Sadly we could not reach a common understanding of this because we have a long history of respect and support for Isengard. If we had talked before I had moved the raid, we most like would have passed on ROV out of friendship.<br>
<br>
Here is ToN reasoning:<br>
<br>
We are not in the NTOV rotation. Thus Clearly and Plainly NOT bound by it.<br>
<br>
ROV has never been part of the NTOV agreement directly anyway but since there are  often dragons left up -- we do ask the rotation Guild if OK before we go. In this case no dragons up and neither my scouts or myself asked.<br>
<br>
My final call was to continue to move on RoV.<br>
<br>
Sorry if this disrupted Isengards plans. <br>
That was not our intent.<br>
<br>
I post this only for the benefit of the Isengard folks. <br>
We wish you well in all that you do, sorry that this misunderstanding arose.  <p>Tose<BR><br>
